<br>
She she rolled up the final scroll to set aside, a messanger knocked lightly at her door.<br>
<br>
&quot;My Queen?&quot; the young girl spoke. &quot;A scroll was recently dropped off at the gates.&quot;<br>
<br>
Alysia stood taking the scroll from the girl.<br>
&quot;Efharisto Lily.&quot; Alysia spoke to the messanger. <br>
<br>
She unrolled the scroll and read it over. A small gasp was let out as she dropped the scroll racing out of her hut.<br>
<br>
She eventually reached the village center over looking her amazon sisters.<br>
<br>
&quot;My sisters, your Queen calls for your assistance in a battle. Eli of the Elisians traveled to the village of Varsith seeking an alliance between the Saurians and the Scynthians. He has been captured.&quot;<br>
<br>
She tried to hold her ground, but it was obvious that pain was stricken in her eyes.<br>
<br>
&quot;We leave now. I ask only the strongest warriors and those that can give true help to our side. Amazons! Move out!&quot; She yelled as she mounted her white mare and rode out the village gates.<br>
<br>
She had already been dressed in her armour. Daggers, crossbow, sais, and of course her sword lined her entire body. She was ready, and she was pissed.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
