<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
         With a violent shove, Eli fell face 1st into the cold wet floor of the prison cell.  A dark and disdained hiss came from behind him as the barred doors came to a clanging close.  The musty air filled the devi's nostrils with a sense of doubt.  Stumbling to his feet, his eyes glanced around his surroundings.  He was in a cell alright.  The walls were made of a reddish bricks of dried clay and rock.. the floor was damp with the smell of sewage.  Beside him was a small torn and stained cot  Eli smirked at the thought of where he will be resting.. the slimy floor or the urine stained bed.  He leaned against the wall, rubbing his arms from the slight chill.  They took away his robes, leaving nothing but his worn pantaloons and his sleeveless tunic.  <br>
        He stepped towards the bars of the cell, peering over to the other prisoners.  Within the other cells he could see captured odusians, with patches of fur burnt or torn off from their flesh.  It was a hideous sight to see.  The air was filled with death and misery.  His eyes fell to the floor with such sadness.  For hours he stood there with his forehead against the bars as his mind drifted from thought to thought.  How he wished he was back at the temple with his daughter Vyi and his wife Alysia.  He was overcome with grief as he did not wish to be here... but for the greater good he needed to be.  As he looked upon the slimy floor, a large reptilian foot came down.  Eli quickly looked upwards to become face to face with his captors.<br>
        &quot;Sss... Emperor shall sssee you now...,&quot; the large lizardman croaked as it began to unlock the door.  Eli cautiously stepped back with a nod as one of the reptiles placed his hands in cuffs and chains and yanked him out of the cell.  Eli had a smile on his face, not because he was going to speak with Corpus to end this war... because he was being pulled out of a cell filled with feces.  <br>
        The devi was brought into a large round room, with many animal heads mounted all along the walls.  Among the animal heads were several amazon heads, which made Eli's heart sank.  He was thrown to the floor, before the throne.  His eyes slowly looked around with caution and up towards the throne.  He saw the feet first, lined with razor sharp talons, and then up the muscular legs... he came up to the chest of a heaving beast, until his eyes met with two dark orange snake like eyes, which narrowed to a slither.  There, upon the throne, sat the Emperor of the Saurian nation, Coprus V'Stakk.  He was larger than the other saurian, who were shorter and more slimmer.  Corpus was muscular and taller.  Upon his head laid a crown, unlike Eli has ever seen.  The crown donned horns and a plate &quot;shield&quot;, much like a triceratops head.  Over his chest was a sash of purple and white, with ancient saurian words stitched in threaded mirthril.  The emperor cocked his head to the side like a curious bird and then leaned over slightly towards the human before him.  Upon all fours, Eli stood perfectly still, not wanting to rile up the king of this city.  Corpus rested back against the throne with a deep haunting laugh.<br>
        &quot;Thisss?!  I ask to bring me amazons and you bring me THISSSS?!!&quot; the king roared, causing a few of the Saurian warriors to jump and squawk in fear.  Eli gulped deeply as he sat on his knees with his eyes down in respect.  Corpus tapped his talons along the arm rest of the throne in a displeased manor.<br>
        &quot;I... am Eli, of the Elisians...,&quot;  Eli whispered.<br>
        Corpus snarled and snorted.<br>
        &quot;I've come to offer you a truce with the Amazon nations...&quot;<br>
        Corpus' eyes widen slightly, as his lips curled to a horrible sneer.  &quot;Truce?&quot; He stomped his foot.  &quot;The amazon filth deserve no truce!&quot; The other saurian nodded in agreement.  &quot;We have been hunted down by them for generation after generation...Sssss... The time for peace has ended.. It is now time for war, mammal!&quot;<br>
        &quot;No!&quot;  Eli stood up.  &quot;We can end this now.  No bloodshed.  No more.  I've seen humans walking through your villages when I was brought here.  What makes them so different from the other humans?&quot;<br>
        Corpus snarled in anger at such disrespect, he leaped out of his throne and before Eli.  With a mighty fist he backhanded Eli across the room. <br>
        &quot;Those hu-monssss...,&quot; Corpus snarled &quot;..Live under Saurian Rule.  They understand the pain and suffering the saurian nations have endured over the centuries and for that they assist us as Allies to the cause.  Among them men and women who equally despise the Nation of Beast Women for their selfish pride.  Ssss...&quot;<br>
        Eli stumbled back to his feet, which surprised Corpus as no one has ever got back up to their feet after a blow from him.  <br>
        &quot;Times have changed.  I assure you that if peace is formed between the two nations that you can form colonies that would guaranty prosperity for both the Amazon and Saurian.&quot;<br>
        The reptile eyed the man oddly, with suspicion..  He began to pace around Eli like a shark ready to drag down a helpless seal into the very blackness of the sea.  Eli stood his ground with his chin up.  <br>
        &quot;Colonies?&quot; Corpus hissed.<br>
        Eli nodded.<br>
        &quot;You are a strange hu-mon, Eel-eye.  Are you a shaman?  Ambassador?&quot;<br>
        &quot;Neither.  I'm mearly a man who wishes no harm to the Saurian or Amazons, only peace.  War is never the answer to anything.  Times have changed, and so have ways.  It is time we fight a war without weapons or... claws.&quot;<br>
        Corpus crawled back into his throne and looked over his shoulder towards the High Shaman Priest of the clan.<br>
        &quot;Sssssire, he is mearly a decoy of the amazonsss... Here to distract us from our thoughtsss..,&quot; growled the Shaman.  &quot;I sensse a god behind him that I've never sssense before.  The hu-mon may be up to sssomething....&quot;<br>
        &quot;I promise you that the only thing I'm up to is restoring the balance between the nations as equals, not rivals,&quot; Eli responded.<br>
        &quot;If you are a friend to Saurian, then prove your wordsss,&quot; haggled Corpus.  <br>
        &quot;If I must prove myself, so be it.&quot;<br>
        Corpus bared his sharp teeth in a toothy grin.  He stepped down from his throne and began to approach Eli.  But before he could reach the devi, a saurian bursted into the room with many cuts and bruises along his body.  It panted and squawked like an injured bird as it limped over to Corpus.  Corpus snarled towards the saurian as it began to chirp and hiss in the saurian language.  Corpus' pupils diolated with anger as he listen, and turned his gaze onto Eli and back to the saurian.  The shaman hissed and snapped at the Devi, also hearing of the news.  Eli backed away slowly, as Corpus leaped onto the throne and pulled out a large scimitar from the display.<br>
        &quot;I knew you were a spy!&quot;  roared Corpus as he leaped back down towards Eli.<br>
        &quot;I don't know what you're talking about!  What's going on?!&quot; shouted Eli.<br>
        &quot;You should know, amazon lover...sss!  I knew you were in league with the Amazons!&quot;  Corpus placed the tip of the blade under Eli's chin.  &quot;Did you think the amazons could get away with kidnapping the Ambassador of Varsith?  You were a fool to come here, Eel-eye.  I will enjoy feasting upon your bones tonight!&quot;<br>
        But before Corpus could make word on his promise, there came a bizarre choo from behind the throne.  Corpus quickly turned his head, as did Eli, to see someone step out from behind.  It was a young human girl.  About 17 in age, 5'7&quot; with a lean figure that could rival the Saurian'.  She was dressed almost like an amazon herself, with a tigerstripe top and loincloth (possibly made from Odusian hide).  Upon her hands were thick leather gauntlets with a large raptor like talon on each one.  Her hair was brown and tied back with a leather strap.  Her tan skinned was pained with jagged stripes, much like the Saurian.  Eli could only blink at this girl, as Corpus pulled away from him.  <br>
        &quot;Leave him be,&quot; smiled the girl as she looked down upon Eli from the throne.<br>
        &quot;He is a spy.  He shall die,&quot; hissed Corpus.<br>
        &quot;Please.. Look at him.  He's harmless.  Do you really think the Amazon scum would bring a man to do their work?&quot;<br>
        Corpus looked to the girl and then back at Eli, who wasn't all that impressive in cold-blooded eyes.<br>
        &quot;You have a point...&quot; groaned the Lizard king.<br>
        The girl smiled and jumped down from the throne and before Eli.  Her brown eyes shimmered like the Saurian, but had a hidden warmth behind them.  <br>
        &quot;Let me keep him.&quot;  she spoke back to Corpus as she inspected and sniffed at Eli.<br>
        &quot;But...&quot;  responded Corpus before he was interrupted by the girl.<br>
        &quot;He is harmless.  And besides... If he does pull anything funny... I'll make sure to gut him myself.&quot;<br>
        Eli blinked again as the girl ordered several Saurian guards to take him to her chambers..<br>
        &quot;Take the hu-mon to her chamber,&quot;  hissed a guard, as he grabbed the chains which binded Eli.  &quot;Keena, daughter of Emperor Corpus, will deal with him now...&quot;<br>
<br>
