<br>
 Dawn's spirit was with them, and she would know the steps of the war, but, due to circumstances she would not go, and would not fight. <br>
<br>
 The Queen of Orio-Pata knew, though, that her son had informed Alysia of her absence and reasoning, and would be noted.<br>
<br>
 But she would not be there. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sartha>Sartha</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 160<br> <font color=#993300>(8/17/01 9:19:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=178.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The War. </span><hr size=1> ::for once, Sartha was not at Dawn's side. No matter what, Sartha was an Amazon before everything, and she would never let her Athelfi go off and fight a war without being there with them. That was the oath she had taken as an Amazon. Her Athelfi and her tribe was her entire world. And so she would stand beside them:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> AthenaCantore</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#993300>(8/18/01 8:36:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=178.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Reply</span><hr size=1> Athena steped out of her hut as she heard Alysia's words. With that she ran back into her hut, sliding her sword into her sheath. She ran back outside and whistled for her horse. As it ran up she jumped up onto it's back. She was always ready for battle, always ready to help. Her emotionaless gaze turned to Alysia as she kicked the side of the mare to step forward.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Amazon Warrioress </span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#993300>(8/19/01 11:59:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=178.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Taking Action</span><hr size=1> Gabriella scurries to her hut, hazel orbs flashing excitedly.  A WAR!  Gabby loves to fight.  Pulling on her armor, she sheathes her sword and amazon staff, as well as some daggers, and her staff of apocolypse.  Kissing the tip of her staff, she slips it into her weapon belt.  Grabbing her bow and arrows she carries them out of the hut, but not before sitting down to write up a poem.  A rallying poem.  For any athelfi not convinced to fight in the war.  She would help fight in more than one way.  After stamping the poem up on the athelfi board so everyone can read, she makes her way to where her queen Alysia awaits....<br>
<br>
<br>
Dreams<br>
<br>
After blowing out the last candle within my hut<br>
I will lay down and my eyes will shut<br>
I will be awake listening for awhile<br>
My memories and happenings of the day all compile<br>
<br>
When the darkness enters my holding<br>
The sleep edges closer and my mind's unfolding<br>
As all my memories cease<br>
And into my head enters a beast<br>
<br>
He is a Saurian, proud and strong<br>
In his eyes he's done no wrong<br>
He tortures helpless men and women<br>
His hate and greed send my dreams spinnin<br>
<br>
I stand up beside my athelfi, weapon in hand<br>
We all show up and take a stand<br>
We fight our hardest, we fight with our hearts<br>
And before it has even seemed like it's started <br>
<br>
The war is over and we still stand<br>
We take our athelfi hand in hand<br>
We sing our amazon war songs loudly<br>
We dance and wave our weapons proudly<br>
<br>
We defeat our enemy and still stand strong<br>
For the saurians have done the wrong<br>
We thank Artemis and Hera alike<br>
And shove the Saurian leader's head on a pike<br>
<br>
